  m_text: Special care has to be taken regarding the quality of the water being fed
    to the boiler. Hard water cannot be fed into the boiler, as it can lead to the
    formation of hard and adherent scales inside the boiler. These scales may cause
    localized overheating, increased fuel consumption, and bursting of water tubes.
    It is therefore necessary to treat the water before feeding it into the boiler.
