      m_Calls: []
  m_text: To safeguard against dangerously low water levels, fusible plugs are fitted
    in the steam drum. These plugs consist of an alloy core with a low melting point.
    When the water level falls and the temperature exceeds the melting point of the
    alloy, the core melts and allows water from the drum to leak into the furnace,
    thereby extinguishing the fire and preventing further overheating. To understand
    this mechanism more clearly, refer to the illustration below.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
